Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: If you find yourself in the position of becoming a caregiver for an Alzheimer’s patient you are most likely overwhelmed with the amount of time, patience, and general lack of knowledge about Alzheimer’s disease. Fear not, you have found a place to get all the answers to all your questions and help you with cope with this dreaded disease. It is our goal and mission to get you the right information, and keep you up to date on everything in the Alzheimer’s world. We are devoted to giving you that information and making your Caregiving experience as easy and as rewarding as possible. After all information is power, power to tackle this job we call Caregiving. For Caregivers that are just starting on this journey we recommend that you read our Guidebook: The Alzheimer's Guidebook For Caregivers it will answer a lot of your questions and make your Caregivng experience more rewarding. We also recommend that you become a member of the Alzheimer's Research Association. And receive all the benefits of full membership. We here at the Alzheimer’s Research Association do not intend for our organization to be in competition with the various organizations that dedicates itself to the race for a cure, but to compliment them by focusing our efforts on just the caregiver.

Full Description: Pravaa enables rapid development of Enterprise Mobility Solutions using its XCell(TM) patent pending mobile platform. Solutions developed using XCell are secure and can be centrally configured, managed and deployed from a single implementation. This enables rapid deployment of cross-platform apps (iOS, Android, Windows) thereby significantly reducing  total costs of ownership. Mobile applications built with Pravaa XCell use server side technology but are native to the device on which they run. Being metadata-driven, they do not need re-installation whenever any updates are made. This drastically reduces ongoing support and maintenance costs, in addition to the development costs. XCell has a flexible integration layer, which integrates seamlessly with existing packaged or custom applications using industry standard methods such as web services and database access. Pravaa XCell may be deployed on-premise within an enterprise network, or in a Cloud environment.

Description: Round Up For Charity Donation Platform
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: GivnGo is an app that allows you to do just that. Help out others in need, whether big or small, by sharing your spare change. GivnGo is a mobile platform which allows users to donate to their favorite charities, schools, and other non-profit organizations. The team at GivnGo has one major motive, which is to make the world a better place by allowing charitable donations to be a part of everyday life. Their ideology is simple: “By sharing your spare change, you can make the world change.” Within the GivnGo app, there are many donation options including one time donations and a monthly recurring option as well. The featured function of the app is called “Round Ups,” which allows users to give back to charity every time they make a purchase by donating their spare change. Users can start “round ups” by linking their main card of purchase (credit or debit) and  also entering their corresponding bank information. You can set monthly limits on how much you donate by adjusting contributions to your own specificity. There is a  $5, $10, $20, and  “no max” setting which caps off the amount given every month, based on whatever a user wants set as their monthly maximum. Watch the pot of gold animation  increase as you give, and see how a little change, can make a big difference for others! The creators for the app like to refer to the the spare change donated as “Karma Coins” (TM). With the GivnGo app every time you shop for some new clothes, buy something to eat, or fill up your gas tank, you are also making an impact on others. This allows you to truly, give and go!

Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: InnerCircle is a mobile app that allows artists to connect with their fans in the most effective and efficient way. Artists can use various modules in order to build a relationship with their fans. The modules are meant to allow artists to gauge fan activity in both the digital and the real world. By quantifying fan activity, artists will now be able to accurately monitor their marketing promotions and analyze how effective these promotions are. In addition to monitoring and growing their fan base, artists have the opportunity to monetize their fan base by incentivising their merchandise or other products using fan support. InnerCircle aims to create a symbiotic relationship between fans and their favorite artists. A platform where fans are rewarded for supporting their favorite artists is meant to create an incentive to further support and appreciate their favorite artists.

Description: ZenoLink develops and implements software applications for the measurement and analysis of human motion.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: ZenoLink, LLC develops and implements software applications for the measurement and analysis of human motion. The company develops applications for use with a 3-D motion capture platform and 3-D motion data that are used to measure human motion, and quantify performance and injury potential. It provides zenoLINK, a biomechanics analysis and training tool that is used to evaluate how and why an athlete jumps, runs, throws, hits, and strikes, as well as to assess and measure biomechanical functions. The company also offers sports-specific progressive skills training and its related functionally specific training programs to athletes to improve their performance, as well as training programs to educate clinicians, coaches, and trainers. Its software is used by athletes, coaches, and trainers primarily in golf, baseball, softball, tennis, lacrosse, cycling, running, and volleyball sports, as well as in healthcare, industrial, and research applications. ZenoLink, LLC was formerly known as welch-e technologies. The company was founded in 2001 and is based in Endicott, New York.
Founders: Chris Welch, George Bock, Mike Welch
